    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "This is the workaround I see for v1:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nsearch.addWidget(\r\n  instantsearch.widgets.refinementList({\r\n    container: '#brand-list',\r\n    attributeName: 'brand',\r\n    // v2 version:\r\n    // transformItems: items => items.filter(item => item.label !== 'Sony'),\r\n    transformData: {\r\n      item(item) {\r\n        if (item.name === 'Sony') {\r\n          // uses a bug in InstantSearch v1,\r\n          // which will not add the classes on empty items\r\n          return {};\r\n        }\r\n        return item;\r\n      },\r\n    },\r\n  })\r\n);\r\n```\r\n\r\nThen you can hide it with css:\r\n\r\n```css\r\n.ais-refinement-list--item label:not(.ais-refinement-list--label) {\r\n  display: none;\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nI updated the sandbox: https://codesandbox.io/s/8k9wqo53pl?module=%2Fsrc%2Fapp.js",
    "created_at": "2018-11-28T09:52:15Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/3309#issuecomment-442386405",
